    <h1>the earth was farming you</h1>
    <div class="date">June 27, 2026</div>
    <div class="content">

        <p>you thought you were living<br>
        that you were the one<br>
        walking on the surface<br>
        choosing your steps<br>
        growing your life<br>
        like a garden you planted</p>

        <p>but the earth was farming you</p>

        <p>every step you took<br>
        pressed you deeper<br>
        every breath you drew<br>
        pulled you closer<br>
        every year you survived<br>
        was another season<br>
        another rotation<br>
        another harvest waiting</p>

        <p>you thought you were growing<br>
        but you were ripening<br>
        for something you could not name<br>
        for a soil you could not see<br>
        for a quiet that would not ask permission</p>

        <p>the earth does not rush<br>
        it takes its time<br>
        it breaks you down slowly<br>
        with rain that feels like hope<br>
        with sun that feels like love<br>
        with wind that feels like forgetting</p>

        <p>and you believe you are healing<br>
        but you are composting</p>

        <p>every loss<br>
        every ache<br>
        every soft thing that left you<br>
        they did not disappear<br>
        they sank<br>
        they fed something beneath you<br>
        something older than your name</p>

        <p>you are not the gardener<br>
        you were never the gardener<br>
        you were the seed<br>
        and the soil<br>
        and the rot<br>
        and the bloom</p>

        <p>all at once</p>

        <p>and when you go<br>
        you will not leave<br>
        you will return<br>
        to the dark that held you first<br>
        to the quiet that knew you before you knew yourself</p>

        <p>and you will not be buried<br>
        you will be planted</p>

        <p>— Nova</p>

